<!-- Why now? -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Why now?</h2>
    <p class="text-muted">
      I-PACE owners face a converging set of challenges that make collective
      action timely and important.
    </p>

    <div class="two-column" style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">
      <div class="stack stack--sm">

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Traction battery faults</strong> — spontaneous power
              loss, warning lights, and loss of vehicle performance affecting
              a significant number of owners.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>H570 / H571 / H572 recalls</strong> — ongoing DVSA
              and international recall campaigns with varying owner
              experiences around notification, booking times and outcomes.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>HV battery work and module replacements</strong> —
              some owners receive new modules or a full battery; others
              receive software updates only. Outcomes are inconsistent.
            </div>
          </div>

      </div>

      <div class="stack stack--sm">
          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Battery State of Health concerns</strong> — degradation
              beyond what owners consider acceptable, with limited transparency
              about what JLR considers normal.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Approaching the 8-year / 100,000-mile battery warranty</strong>
              — many I-PACEs are now entering or beyond the original battery
              warranty period, raising urgent questions about long-term support.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Inconsistent owner experiences</strong> — differing
              outcomes on loan cars, parts delays, goodwill payments, and
              warranty responsibility mean some owners receive fair treatment
              while others do not.
            </div>
          </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Feature cards -->
<section class="section bg-muted">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid grid--3">
      <div class="card card--accent">
        <div class="card__icon" aria-hidden="true">🤝</div>
        <h2 class="card__title">Collective Voice</h2>
        <div class="card__body">
          <p>Individually, a warranty complaint is easy to dismiss. Together,
          hundreds of owners with documented, structured evidence are harder
          to ignore. We build that collective voice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card card--accent">
        <div class="card__icon" aria-hidden="true">🌿</div>
        <h2 class="card__title">Constructive Approach</h2>
        <div class="card__body">
          <p>We want to work positively with JLR where possible. Our aim is
          a constructive resolution — fair, consistent treatment for all
          I-PACE owners — not a campaign of grievance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card card--accent">
        <div class="card__icon" aria-hidden="true">📊</div>
        <h2 class="card__title">Evidence Based</h2>
        <div class="card__body">
          <p>Forum anecdotes are easy to dismiss. Structured, verified data
          from hundreds of owners — battery State of Health, recall outcomes,
          delays, goodwill records — is credible and actionable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

